{
  "stem": "6773.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if somebody got killed outside from-- from Jews, I had to go out with another guy and take them to the burial, to the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the end of this three years period-- let me tell you before the end of that time-- while we were in camp there in the factory, we were planning to run out.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was made a plan complete with everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I used to steal guns and grenades from the Gestapo because they never checked me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I was working in the Gestapo, I used to steal them there and the magazines.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had a [GERMAN] which they picked us up every day, every morning to work, and 4:30, they used to take us all back to the camp.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He used to take out his Browning, his gun.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he said, you see this gun?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "With this gun I'm going to shoot you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I told him, I'm dead already a long time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You can't do anything to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was about every couple of days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He repeated and repeated until it happened he was the [? magaziner ?] of the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And one day the chief of the Gestapo went up to the magazine, he just wanted to take a look.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And before he go to the magazine, there was a watchman, a German from the Gestapo, and he had a list what was stored in the magazine.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So he took from him the list and he goes into the-- to the magazine, and he-- he looks.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He looks what they're there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Ten bags of sugar.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There's not one left.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There's 10 bags of potatoes that was left too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So there was a lot of things left.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
